<tree mode="full" root="false" taxon="Definition"><frontmatter><addr>jms-0033</addr> <route>jms-0033.xml</route> <date>March 5, 2023</date> <authors><author><a href="jonmsterling.xml" class="local" rel="author">Jonathan Sterling</a></author> </authors> <title>Carrable map</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A morphism \({E} \xrightarrow{p} {B}\) in a category \(\mathcal{C}\) is said to be <em>carrable</em> when for any \({A} \xrightarrow{f} {B}\), the pullback \({E \times _ {B} A} \xrightarrow{f^*p} {A}\) depicted below exists.</p><center><img src="resources/1044d43b7e1d8ea2b744e713880b62ca.svg"/></center></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related/> <backlinks><tree mode="full" root="false" taxon="Definition"><frontmatter><addr>jms-0031</addr> <route>jms-0031.xml</route> <date>March 5, 2023</date> <authors><author><a href="jonmsterling.xml" class="local" rel="author">Jonathan Sterling</a></author> </authors> <title>Exponentiable Arrow</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <a href="jms-0033.xml" class="local">carrable map</a> \({E} \xrightarrow{p} {B}\) in a category \(\mathcal{C}\) is said to be <em>exponentiable</em> when it is <a href="jms-0032.xml" class="local">exponentiable</a> when viewed as an object of the slice category \({\mathcal{C}} _ {/ B}\).</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>